<p>For a fictional character, Sherlock Holmes has a strangely real presence in the physical world. This plaque is posted near the Reichenbach Falls in Switzerland:</p>
<figure id="attachment_71144" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-71144" style="width: 500px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-06-plaque-buildup-1.jpg" alt="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Sherlock_Holmes_plaque.jpg" width="500" height="757" class="size-full wp-image-71144" srcset="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-06-plaque-buildup-1.jpg 500w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-06-plaque-buildup-1-300x454.jpg 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-71144" class="wp-caption-text">Image: <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Sherlock_Holmes_plaque.jpg">Wikimedia Commons</a></figcaption></figure>
<p>This one&#8217;s on a cottage in Sussex:</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-06-plaque-buildup-2.jpg" alt="sussex holmes plaque" width="922" height="682" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-71145" srcset="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-06-plaque-buildup-2.jpg 922w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-06-plaque-buildup-2-600x444.jpg 600w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-06-plaque-buildup-2-300x222.jpg 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 922px) 100vw, 922px" /></p>
<p>There&#8217;s even a plaque <a href="https://www.futilitycloset.com/2012/06/16/afoot/">at the spot where Holmes met Watson</a>.</p>
<p>Naturalist Gilbert White, author of <em>Natural History and Antiquities of Selborne</em>, seems to have had an imaginary contemporary nemesis. Someone has posted this plaque on the house opposite White&#8217;s 18th-century Hampshire home:</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-06-plaque-buildup-3.jpg" alt="sullivan black plaque" width="800" height="784" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-71146" srcset="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-06-plaque-buildup-3.jpg 800w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-06-plaque-buildup-3-600x588.jpg 600w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-06-plaque-buildup-3-300x294.jpg 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></p>
<p>(Black is the opposite of white, and Sullivan is the opposite, or at least the complement, of Gilbert.)</p>
<p>Finally, this plaque adorns the Park Street Eye Clinic in Tauranga, New Zealand:</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-06-plaque-buildup-4.jpg" alt="nz plaque" width="800" height="601" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-71147" srcset="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-06-plaque-buildup-4.jpg 800w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-06-plaque-buildup-4-600x451.jpg 600w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/2025-07-06-plaque-buildup-4-300x225.jpg 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></p>
<p>Accurate enough.</p>
